<i>♪ Yes, I know ♪♪</i>

04:02.702 --> 04:06.705
The Monfell Shipping Center has been
non-operational for the last six months.

04:06.706 --> 04:10.417
Since its closure, it's become
a favorite location for São Paulo Locos...

04:10.418 --> 04:11.627
...to conduct business.

04:11.628 --> 04:15.172
They've come and gone as they please
with minimal resistance.

04:15.173 --> 04:17.423
That ends today.

04:17.425 --> 04:21.428
Late last night, a shipping container
arrived at Monfell from Bogotá.

04:21.428 --> 04:22.930
Due to the amount of chatter...

04:22.931 --> 04:26.725
...DEA believes this could be their
largest shipment of contraband to date.

04:26.726 --> 04:29.186
The source couldn't identify exactly
what came in.

04:29.187 --> 04:32.856
So whether it's money, arms,
or the ghost of Pablo Escobar, be ready.

04:32.857 --> 04:35.442
Secure the scene,
help find the container.

04:35.443 --> 04:39.313
Once you've done that,
you all can go enjoy your holiday.

04:45.078 --> 04:46.745
HALL:
We're just barbecuing.

04:46.746 --> 04:48.246
It's a whole thing.

04:48.247 --> 04:50.791
- How about you?
GUTIERREZ: I don't really have any plans.

04:50.792 --> 04:52.668
- You should come over.
- Yeah?

04:52.669 --> 04:55.295
Yeah. Carley and Becky
would love to see you.

04:55.296 --> 04:57.623
Not me. I'm sick to death of you.

04:59.467 --> 05:01.176
Sorry to ruin your holiday.

05:01.177 --> 05:04.012
Aw, you ruin every day, El.
Why should today be the exception?

05:04.013 --> 05:05.923
Don't call me "El."

05:07.684 --> 05:09.351
When did this come down?

05:09.352 --> 05:11.720
Got the call from DEA at 2. Why?

05:12.146 --> 05:15.273
HALL: A little short notice.
DWYER: We've had shorter.

05:15.274 --> 05:17.518
Yeah.

05:18.736 --> 05:22.322
Don't get that big brain of yours thinking.
It only gets you in trouble.

05:22.323 --> 05:25.984
- Inspiring as always.
DWYER: And don't fuck up.

05:31.332 --> 05:33.367
Let's go.

05:38.047 --> 05:40.874
Ward? Hello?

05:41.551 --> 05:43.719
WARD: What's this?
PHOENIX: What we're looking for.

05:43.720 --> 05:45.971
- Yeah, it's pretty.
BENSON: Hey, Chu.

05:45.972 --> 05:47.139
CHU:
Mm.

05:47.140 --> 05:49.641
Why don't you come to the beach later?
I'm having a party.

05:49.642 --> 05:51.268
No, I got plans.

05:51.269 --> 05:53.270
BENSON: It's your loss.
PHIL: Benson.

05:53.271 --> 05:56.189
- Why would she go to your party?
- Aren't you too old for this?

05:56.190 --> 05:58.308
Just entering my prime.

05:58.443 --> 06:01.403
Yo, I'm not doing anything.
How come I didn't get an invite?

06:01.404 --> 06:03.405
Remember what happened
last time you came?

06:03.406 --> 06:05.782
- No.
- Ask his wife.

06:05.783 --> 06:07.484
ALL:
Oh!

06:08.870 --> 06:10.162
HALL:
All right, simmer down.

06:10.163 --> 06:12.372
Simmer down.

06:12.373 --> 06:14.499
A little calm-before-the-storm levity.

06:14.500 --> 06:17.002
There's not gonna be a storm.

06:17.003 --> 06:20.205
- What makes you say that?
WEIR: They've been getting lazy.

06:20.381 --> 06:22.507
We've been letting them
do a few scores...

06:22.508 --> 06:25.419
- ...and now they feel safe.
- Hmm.

06:25.928 --> 06:29.381
Well, I guess we got all dolled up
for nothing.

06:35.772 --> 06:38.474
[♪♪♪]

06:54.207 --> 06:56.708
HALL [OVER RADIO]:
<i>I don't give a damn what the DEA says.</i>

06:56.709 --> 06:59.920
<i>We go in heavy, stay frosty.</i>

06:59.921 --> 07:01.838
<i>Watch each other's backs...</i>

07:01.839 --> 07:04.883
<i>...stick to the plan, stay tight.</i>

07:04.884 --> 07:07.336
<i>Let's do this.</i>

07:10.598 --> 07:12.925
[♪♪♪]

07:48.302 --> 07:51.713
CHU: Drop the phone and keep
your hands where I can see them.

07:55.059 --> 07:57.719
That was sloppy, Chu.

07:58.104 --> 08:01.398
All, we have guard one on lockdown.
Surveillance is ours.

08:01.399 --> 08:03.108
HALL:
<i>Copy.</i>

08:03.109 --> 08:04.609
WARD:
The yard's clear.

08:04.610 --> 08:08.564
We got another guard
on the east-side stairwell.

08:08.823 --> 08:10.198
Hands. Now.

08:10.199 --> 08:12.276
WEIR:
Clear.

08:12.535 --> 08:14.820
Knees.

08:15.496 --> 08:16.746
How many others are there?

08:16.747 --> 08:19.032
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

08:19.250 --> 08:21.001
Sofi, anything?

08:21.002 --> 08:23.420
Nothing. This was supposed
to be a shipping yard.

08:23.421 --> 08:26.415
- I don't see any containers.
HALL: <i>Copy that.</i>

08:26.924 --> 08:30.343
Come on, do you have to do that?

08:30.344 --> 08:31.928
Sorry.

08:31.929 --> 08:34.298
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

08:36.558 --> 08:38.351
You sure this is the right place?

08:38.352 --> 08:40.888
This is the place.

08:44.232 --> 08:46.393
Let's go.

09:26.025 --> 09:28.193
- Jackpot.
- Copy. Where are you?

09:28.194 --> 09:30.403
Outside.
Northwest side of the warehouse.

09:30.404 --> 09:32.280
Copy. Ward, stay where you are.

09:32.281 --> 09:35.283
Everyone else,
meet at the shipping container.

09:35.284 --> 09:37.402
Copy that.

09:49.924 --> 09:51.667
Look to your left.

09:52.510 --> 09:55.754
Copy. Straight ahead, guys.

09:57.598 --> 10:00.934
I've got 10 to 12 hostiles coming in hot
from inside the warehouse.

10:00.935 --> 10:03.845
<i>Take cover. Take cover.</i>

10:19.245 --> 10:21.363
GUTIERREZ:
Take cover.

10:59.452 --> 11:01.611
Cover me.

11:11.172 --> 11:12.964
- You okay?
- I'm all right.

11:12.965 --> 11:15.375
I got you covered. Go.

11:24.018 --> 11:25.643
[GRUNTING]

11:25.644 --> 11:27.062
[GROANING]

11:27.063 --> 11:29.473
PHIL:
Gotta get her out.

11:40.576 --> 11:42.903
[GRUNTS]

11:46.123 --> 11:47.916
Stay down. You're gonna be okay.

11:47.917 --> 11:49.918
Are you hit?

11:49.919 --> 11:52.412
Just got the vest.

12:03.599 --> 12:05.300
[SCREAMS]

12:07.019 --> 12:09.763
- Cover.
- Go, go, go.

12:25.663 --> 12:27.739
[BONE CRACKS
THEN MAN SCREAMS]

12:36.090 --> 12:37.966
Now you're both being sloppy.

12:37.967 --> 12:40.168
You owe me a beer.

12:40.261 --> 12:41.469
[GROANS]

12:41.470 --> 12:43.596
DIEGO: Let go. Let go.
- Little help here.

12:43.597 --> 12:45.799
DIEGO:
My arm.

12:46.809 --> 12:48.601
- My arm!
HOOKS: Yard's secure.

12:48.602 --> 12:51.896
DIEGO: My arm!
- Whoa. Whoa, whoa.

12:51.897 --> 12:53.682
What the fuck?

12:55.693 --> 12:57.569
It's a fucking suicide vest.

12:57.570 --> 13:00.029
- What are you wearing this for?
- Go fuck yourself.

13:00.030 --> 13:01.531
WARD:
Inside's secure.

13:01.532 --> 13:03.283
What the fuck?

13:03.284 --> 13:05.076
PHOENIX:
<i>We need an ambulance.</i>

13:05.077 --> 13:06.619
BENSON:
<i>I'm on it.</i>

13:06.620 --> 13:09.038
Fuck. Phil.

13:09.039 --> 13:11.116
[♪♪♪]

13:13.502 --> 13:15.420
No.

13:15.421 --> 13:18.665
I got Phoenix. Let me see
if it went through your vest.

13:24.763 --> 13:26.715
[PHOENIX GRUNTS]

13:27.141 --> 13:29.467
I got you.

13:36.358 --> 13:39.394
"It's not gonna be a storm."

13:44.074 --> 13:45.901
Cover!

14:24.990 --> 14:27.817
[♪♪♪]

14:50.307 --> 14:52.842
Cut him down.

14:54.520 --> 14:56.646
HALL: I don't know why
some crazy motherfucker...

14:56.647 --> 14:59.107
...would put on a suicide vest.

14:59.108 --> 15:02.068
That's not our problem anymore.

15:02.069 --> 15:03.812
All right, fine.

15:03.904 --> 15:05.697
- Let me go. My arm.
GUTIERREZ: That's Diego.

15:05.698 --> 15:08.825
He won't shut up,
and the guy we cut down's not talking.

15:08.826 --> 15:10.159
What'd Dwyer say?

15:10.160 --> 15:12.161
She's sending a wagon.

15:12.162 --> 15:13.496
What?

15:13.497 --> 15:15.915
- Why?
- She wants us to bring them in.

15:15.916 --> 15:18.626
- I thought this was DEA.
- The DEA guys are dead.

15:18.627 --> 15:20.461
She can't get ahold of brass.

15:20.462 --> 15:21.713
WARD:
Fucking Fourth.

15:21.714 --> 15:23.756
Till she does, we hang onto them.

15:23.757 --> 15:26.009
We should keep them. Fuck the DEA.

15:26.010 --> 15:28.136
Fuck them all.
These assholes killed Phil.

15:28.137 --> 15:31.923
- They should defer to us.
- We're bringing them in.

15:34.602 --> 15:36.761
GUTIERREZ:
What a mess.

15:45.237 --> 15:46.904
LARS:
Most are under the impression...

15:46.905 --> 15:49.782
...that since the Southern states
were in favor of slavery...

15:49.783 --> 15:52.535
...that they insisted on
the Three-Fifths Compromise...

15:52.536 --> 15:55.371
...found in Article 1, Section 2
of the Constitution...

15:55.372 --> 15:59.125
...that determined that slaves
are only worth three-fifths a person.

15:59.126 --> 16:02.670
It was, in fact, the North that did this.

16:02.671 --> 16:06.299
The South would have loved
to have counted each slave twice...

16:06.300 --> 16:08.384
...and the North, rightly so...

16:08.385 --> 16:11.679
...didn't believe that the slaves
that didn't have the right to vote...

16:11.680 --> 16:14.599
...should count equally
to those that did.

16:14.600 --> 16:17.977
That would've given the South
more power...

16:17.978 --> 16:20.513
...to put their influence on the North.

16:21.023 --> 16:23.141
And what's your point?

16:23.692 --> 16:25.852
I thought we were chatting.

16:29.615 --> 16:32.192
[BUZZING]

16:36.747 --> 16:37.955
Yes?

16:37.956 --> 16:41.084
MAN [IN ALTERED VOICE]: <i>You've
come an awful long way for nothing.</i>

16:41.085 --> 16:43.503
It's not that far. Who is this?

16:43.504 --> 16:45.296
<i>Just listen.</i>

16:45.297 --> 16:47.006
<i>Diego fucked up.</i>

16:47.007 --> 16:49.959
<i>He lost Scorpion.</i>

16:50.719 --> 16:52.136
And you have him?

16:52.137 --> 16:53.471
[OVER SPEAKERPHONE]
<i>Not that simple.</i>

16:53.472 --> 16:56.182
<i>But I know where he is
and how to get him.</i>

16:56.183 --> 16:57.392
<i>Fifty million.</i>

16:57.393 --> 17:00.019
<i>We both know he's worth 10 times that.</i>

17:00.020 --> 17:02.522
I don't think this is a game
you wanna play.

17:02.523 --> 17:06.223
- You don't know who you're dealing...
<i>- I'll be in touch with instructions.</i>

17:09.070 --> 17:10.855
...with.

17:12.156 --> 17:15.367
Two hundred years ago, it was
so much easier to buy a human being.

17:15.368 --> 17:17.744
- Check out his story.
- If it's true?

17:17.746 --> 17:19.789
It's fucking Scorpion.

17:19.790 --> 17:21.624
I don't wanna lose him.

17:21.625 --> 17:25.994
Not now. Not again.

17:26.088 --> 17:28.455
[♪♪♪]

17:45.816 --> 17:48.059
HALL:
York.

17:48.235 --> 17:51.195
We're short-handed.
Help Sofi process our guests.

17:51.196 --> 17:52.530
Got it, commander.

17:52.531 --> 17:55.024
[DIEGO SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

17:55.534 --> 17:59.487
- My arm! It's fucking broken.
- I'll break your other one. Move it.

18:04.918 --> 18:06.661
Move.

18:17.347 --> 18:19.340
[SIGHS]

18:24.146 --> 18:25.938
I thought I made myself clear.

18:25.939 --> 18:27.607
We got jumped, and not by some...

18:27.608 --> 18:30.276
You say that, and all I hear
is you weren't prepared.

18:30.277 --> 18:32.862
What happened? Your team take it easy
because it's a holiday?

18:32.863 --> 18:34.238
What was the DEA onto?

18:34.239 --> 18:36.949
- What do you mean?
- Come on, Ellen. This is so fucked.

18:36.950 --> 18:40.495
- Clearly, they weren't honest with us.
- All we know is what they told us.

18:40.496 --> 18:44.248
They acted on a tip that 500 million
in product was moving through Monfell.

18:44.249 --> 18:46.959
Ah. And what's it turn out to be? Hmm?

18:46.960 --> 18:48.836
A guy in a box.

18:48.837 --> 18:51.506
Protected by heavily armed
São Paulo Locos soldiers...

18:51.507 --> 18:54.342
Their tip was wrong.
What do you want me to say?

18:54.343 --> 18:57.128
That doesn't make them fucking liars.

19:01.809 --> 19:03.851
So, what do we do now?

19:03.852 --> 19:06.930
I have calls in. No one's around.

19:06.980 --> 19:08.773
Until we get answers, we sit tight.

19:08.774 --> 19:11.359
- Fuck that. I'm gonna talk to them.
- No, you're not.

19:11.360 --> 19:12.777
You're gonna leave them be.

19:12.778 --> 19:15.363
- They're the feds' problem.
- Jesus Christ.

19:15.364 --> 19:18.566
Phil is dead.
Don't you wanna know why?

19:18.575 --> 19:23.246
Right now all I'm thinking about
is what I'm gonna tell his family.

19:23.247 --> 19:25.949
[♪♪♪]

19:29.545 --> 19:32.789
MR. MAGOO [ON TV]:
<i>Elevator to lobby.</i>

19:32.923 --> 19:35.049
<i>Fine.</i>

19:35.050 --> 19:37.426
<i>Lobby, please.</i>

19:37.427 --> 19:38.803
[DOORBELL RINGS]

19:38.804 --> 19:40.429
<i>Watch those sudden stops, boy.</i>

19:40.430 --> 19:43.049
<i>Somebody could get hurt.</i>

19:43.767 --> 19:46.018
<i>It's a big place.</i>

19:46.019 --> 19:50.682
<i>And they've got their
Christmas decorations up already.</i>

19:54.236 --> 19:56.279
LARS:
Nicholas.

19:56.280 --> 19:59.857
Mr. C. I wasn't, um....

20:00.659 --> 20:03.736
Make yourselves at home.

20:06.164 --> 20:07.373
Welcome.

20:07.374 --> 20:10.501
MR. MAGOO: <i>Confound it,
somebody better nail that down.</i>

20:10.502 --> 20:12.753
<i>Could take a nasty fall
from a loose board.</i>

20:12.754 --> 20:14.922
Oh, I just....

20:14.923 --> 20:16.591
<i>Lord help the whole thing.</i>

20:16.592 --> 20:19.010
Nicholas. Did you do what I asked?

20:19.011 --> 20:20.761
Yes, yes. Yes.

20:20.762 --> 20:25.091
I did. Let me just show you.

20:26.351 --> 20:30.980
So I was able to tap into a security
camera across from the shipping center.

20:30.981 --> 20:32.356
Where did they take him?

20:32.357 --> 20:34.650
S.W.A.T.'s got him back at their place.

20:34.651 --> 20:37.486
It's their renovated facility
in the middle of nowhere.

20:37.487 --> 20:40.940
- Sounds like the paint isn't even dry yet.
- How do you know?

20:41.033 --> 20:43.910
I heard it on my police scanner.

20:43.911 --> 20:45.578
LARS:
Well done, Nicholas.

20:45.579 --> 20:47.614
Now...

20:48.123 --> 20:50.625
...can you trace the number
that called this phone?

20:50.626 --> 20:52.960
Find out who and where they are?

20:52.961 --> 20:55.872
- I can try.
- Try hard.

20:58.008 --> 21:02.003
Uh, of course. No problem.

21:06.516 --> 21:11.429
DWYER: Melissa, Phil pulled Phoenix out
of harm's way just before he got shot.

21:12.439 --> 21:15.058
He was a hero.

21:17.235 --> 21:18.978
Yes.

21:19.738 --> 21:22.073
You have my word.

21:22.074 --> 21:25.568
Whoever's responsible for this
is gonna pay.

21:27.037 --> 21:29.038
HALL [OVER PHONE]:
<i>I'm sorry. I can't leave now.</i>

21:29.039 --> 21:34.077
No, I understand.
Should I cancel today?

21:34.294 --> 21:35.836
No, don't do that.

21:35.837 --> 21:38.506
<i>- You okay?</i>
- Yeah. Yeah.

21:38.507 --> 21:39.715
Travis?

21:39.716 --> 21:41.793
<i>Yeah?</i>

21:41.969 --> 21:45.338
I'm really sorry.

21:45.347 --> 21:47.715
I love you.

21:52.562 --> 21:54.772
It's our turn
to host the holiday barbecue...

21:54.773 --> 21:59.902
...so Carley's at home making the food
for 22 kids and their parents.

21:59.903 --> 22:03.606
- What's up?
- Elson called. Said to come down.

22:04.908 --> 22:06.492
GUTIERREZ:
Carley still mad at you?

22:06.493 --> 22:08.786
She's not mad at me.

22:08.787 --> 22:10.454
Sorry, man, I'm on her side.

22:10.455 --> 22:13.332
What...? There's no side.
She's not mad at me.

22:13.333 --> 22:15.918
Besides, you can't be on her side.
You're my partner.

22:15.919 --> 22:17.712
That's a brotherhood.

22:17.713 --> 22:19.505
Yeah, but Carley's like my sister.

22:19.506 --> 22:22.341
- And sisterhood trumps brotherhood...
- That's bullshit.

22:22.342 --> 22:24.093
Look...

22:24.094 --> 22:27.138
...you decided before you got married
that you only wanted one kid.

22:27.139 --> 22:28.848
Yeah. That was like 10 years ago.

22:28.849 --> 22:31.308
But out of the blue,
you say you want another kid.

22:31.309 --> 22:34.729
Yeah, I said maybe we could think
about having another kid...

22:34.730 --> 22:37.807
- ...then it became...
- You wanna know what she heard?

22:37.816 --> 22:41.444
You wanna have another baby
that she'll have to carry for nine months.

22:41.445 --> 22:44.780
She's gonna have to walk away
from work after all she's accomplished.

22:44.781 --> 22:48.200
She's gonna wake up 10 times a night
to feed and change the kid...

22:48.201 --> 22:51.195
...because you're always off doing this.

22:51.872 --> 22:55.658
- She heard all that with "maybe"?
- Yes.

22:57.711 --> 22:58.919
ELSON:
I don't know.

22:58.920 --> 23:02.048
No, no, no, dude.
It just keeps coming up with an error.

23:02.049 --> 23:04.508
I don't know.
It's some sort of remote-access bug.

23:04.509 --> 23:06.218
Have you ever seen it?

23:06.219 --> 23:08.971
Yeah, I tried that. I tried that.

23:08.972 --> 23:10.347
Oh, are you kidding me?

23:10.348 --> 23:13.092
- I had that in the queue.
- While we're young.

23:13.894 --> 23:15.519
I gotta go.

23:15.520 --> 23:17.346
Please don't touch that.

23:18.482 --> 23:19.732
What do you got?

23:19.733 --> 23:22.401
Our friend Diego is a bad, bad dude.

23:22.402 --> 23:24.278
From Honduras, okay?

23:24.279 --> 23:27.698
Joined the São Paulo Locos,
known as the S.P.L., when he was 6.

23:27.699 --> 23:29.200
He's now a lieutenant.

23:29.201 --> 23:32.828
- Okay. What about our mystery man?
ELSON: Scorpion?

23:32.829 --> 23:34.497
Is that what we're calling him?

23:34.498 --> 23:36.415
Yeah, for now.

23:36.416 --> 23:38.709
Nada on him.
He's not in any active database.

23:38.710 --> 23:41.796
What about other databases?

23:41.797 --> 23:45.500
- Such as?
- FBI? CIA? DoD?

23:45.842 --> 23:48.135
I don't have clearance to tap those.

23:48.136 --> 23:51.222
But you could probably do it
without clearance, right?

23:51.223 --> 23:53.257
Are you asking me or telling?

23:53.433 --> 23:57.019
There's no way a guy protected
by S.P.L.'s best is a ghost.

23:57.020 --> 23:58.562
Just find out who he is.

23:58.563 --> 24:00.439
You got it, boss.

24:00.440 --> 24:02.525
Hey, put Diego in room one.

24:02.526 --> 24:05.611
- Get him to talk, have Ward listen.
- What are you gonna do?

24:05.612 --> 24:08.531
I'm gonna go talk to Scorpion.

24:08.532 --> 24:10.866
Dwyer's gonna lose her shit.

24:10.867 --> 24:13.611
Let me worry about Dwyer.

24:15.622 --> 24:16.997
[MUMBLING IN SPANISH]

24:16.998 --> 24:19.075
[DOOR BUZZES]

24:22.379 --> 24:25.331
Hey, Diego. We meet again.

24:25.382 --> 24:26.841
You broke my fucking arm.

24:26.842 --> 24:29.426
I gave you the choice
to have your arm broken or not.

24:29.427 --> 24:31.679
You chose poorly.

24:31.680 --> 24:34.515
Now, explain something to me.

24:34.516 --> 24:37.969
Why would a lieutenant be put
on babysitting duty?

24:38.979 --> 24:40.688
Did they demote you, Diego?

24:40.689 --> 24:42.231
Go fuck yourself, <i>puta.</i>

24:42.232 --> 24:45.685
- Who's the man in the box?
- You wanna know who he is?

24:47.529 --> 24:49.355
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

24:49.531 --> 24:52.733
That's who he is.
He's the fucking devil.

24:56.413 --> 24:59.073
Want something to drink?

25:00.000 --> 25:03.544
You need a medic. It's a holiday,
but I could have it arranged.

25:03.545 --> 25:06.539
Am I being charged with a crime?

25:06.840 --> 25:08.833
That depends.

25:08.925 --> 25:12.003
- On?
- Who are you?

25:12.679 --> 25:15.756
Have you asked Diego who I am?

25:17.100 --> 25:19.468
[MUMBLING IN SPANISH]

25:19.603 --> 25:21.770
What's that?

25:21.771 --> 25:24.440
He said that this was going to happen.

25:24.441 --> 25:27.276
- Who said...?
- He said they'd come and he'd escape.

25:27.277 --> 25:28.861
Who would escape? Diego...

25:28.862 --> 25:31.981
You're all fucking dead.
You don't know it.

25:38.580 --> 25:40.740
You tell them I did this, okay?

25:42.751 --> 25:44.785
You tell them I did this.

25:46.755 --> 25:48.789
Hey, stop.

25:49.424 --> 25:51.425
Diego, stop! Help!

25:51.426 --> 25:53.260
I need some help in here.

25:53.261 --> 25:55.796
Perhaps you should attend to that.

26:00.268 --> 26:02.094
GUTIERREZ:
Stop it!

26:05.273 --> 26:08.517
Oh, God.

26:22.165 --> 26:24.909
What the fuck happened?

26:25.293 --> 26:27.836
WARD:
He just impaled himself.

26:27.837 --> 26:30.206
HALL:
You're kidding me.

26:30.590 --> 26:33.125
Fuck me.

26:37.973 --> 26:39.799
[DOOR BUZZES]

26:50.735 --> 26:52.653
Who the fuck are you?

26:52.654 --> 26:54.405
You have blood on your hands.

26:54.406 --> 26:57.283
Answer the question.

26:57.284 --> 26:59.201
Did you kill him?

26:59.202 --> 27:00.536
No.

27:00.537 --> 27:02.246
He killed himself.

27:02.247 --> 27:04.540
Cracked his skull wide open.

27:04.541 --> 27:07.034
We do not have much time.

27:07.085 --> 27:09.086
I'm not asking again.

27:09.087 --> 27:11.797
What is important is that you listen.

27:11.798 --> 27:14.717
You may think
the events of today were in error...

27:14.718 --> 27:17.428
...but I assure you, my friend,
they were not.

27:17.429 --> 27:20.423
You better start
answering my questions.

27:20.890 --> 27:25.436
I have information in my head
worth billions of dollars.

27:25.437 --> 27:26.979
What kind of information?

27:26.980 --> 27:29.189
The kind that can set the world on fire.

27:29.190 --> 27:32.359
Jesus Christ,
enough with the fucking riddles.

27:32.360 --> 27:34.778
Fine. Here is the truth.

27:34.779 --> 27:38.866
Very soon, you will be told that officers
from a federal agency are here...

27:38.867 --> 27:40.743
...to take me into custody.

27:40.744 --> 27:43.912
They are not what they say they are.

27:43.913 --> 27:46.790
Do not let these men take me.

27:46.791 --> 27:51.662
Do this, and I will help you
to survive what is coming next.

27:59.596 --> 28:01.555
- FBI's here for him now.
- What?

28:01.556 --> 28:03.015
I told you I had calls in.

28:03.016 --> 28:06.635
We're handing him over,
so we can all go home.

28:08.605 --> 28:10.814
- Did they say who he was?
- A known terrorist.

28:10.815 --> 28:13.893
Someone they've been after
for a while.

28:15.737 --> 28:18.155
- Where are they?
- Lobby.

28:18.156 --> 28:20.366
I'll take care of it.

28:20.367 --> 28:23.110
I'll bring them to him, pass him off.

28:28.124 --> 28:30.167
Gentlemen, you're here for the prisoner.

28:30.168 --> 28:33.420
Commander Hall. I'm Agent Franklin.
My partner, Agent Cox.

28:33.421 --> 28:35.672
- Sorry for the delay.
- No problem.

28:35.673 --> 28:38.258
We appreciate you hanging on
to our guy.

28:38.259 --> 28:40.711
Right this way.

28:42.889 --> 28:46.133
That's funny,
I thought all you FBI guys used Berettas.

28:47.394 --> 28:49.061
These are our personal weapons.

28:49.062 --> 28:52.848
- On the job?
- It's a holiday.

28:52.857 --> 28:57.069
So, what'd this guy do
to get on your database, anyway?

28:57.070 --> 29:00.114
- Terrorist stuff.
- Things we're not at liberty to discuss.

29:00.115 --> 29:03.609
"Terrorist stuff." What's his name?

29:04.869 --> 29:09.573
Come on. His name can't be a matter
of national security.

29:12.460 --> 29:16.997
Well, look, it's clear you guys
aren't FBI, so no fooling.

29:17.549 --> 29:19.875
Who are you?

29:22.804 --> 29:25.389
Just hand the prisoner over.

29:25.390 --> 29:27.591
Not until I get some answers.

29:31.438 --> 29:34.265
[♪♪♪]

29:37.527 --> 29:39.270
[GUNSHOT]

29:56.087 --> 29:57.838
You are dead, motherfucker.

29:57.839 --> 30:00.541
- Drop the knife now!
- Now!

30:00.633 --> 30:02.593
CHU:
Hands on your head.

30:02.594 --> 30:04.336
Knees.

30:06.097 --> 30:09.057
- You all right, commander?
- Prick.

30:09.058 --> 30:11.677
- Got him?
- Yeah, we got him.

30:13.605 --> 30:15.063
Commander?

30:15.064 --> 30:16.807
Commander.

30:17.859 --> 30:20.186
[♪♪♪]

31:03.863 --> 31:05.447
[GUN COCKS]

31:05.448 --> 31:08.234
[♪♪♪]

31:29.389 --> 31:31.507
You trust me now?

31:32.141 --> 31:33.892
[DOOR BUZZES]

31:33.893 --> 31:35.894
Hooks.

31:35.895 --> 31:38.472
Hands on your head.

31:38.565 --> 31:39.898
Let's go.

31:39.899 --> 31:43.269
- You all right, commander?
- Yeah, yeah.

31:56.541 --> 31:58.701
WARD:
Keep moving.

32:02.422 --> 32:04.665
[FRANKLIN CACKLING]

32:05.925 --> 32:08.218
Keys, cowboy.

32:08.219 --> 32:11.471
I'm going to enjoy watching you die.

32:11.472 --> 32:13.257
Shut the fuck up.

32:14.350 --> 32:16.435
Everything happened the way he said.

32:16.436 --> 32:20.105
Our mystery man's not even
in the FBI's database.

32:20.106 --> 32:22.599
Wait. How do you know that?

32:24.652 --> 32:27.112
You hacked the FBI database?

32:27.113 --> 32:29.114
Just a bit.

32:29.115 --> 32:31.199
Look, on the way
to the shipping center...

32:31.200 --> 32:34.536
...I made a crack to Weir about this
being the calm before the storm...

32:34.537 --> 32:36.747
...and he said
there wasn't gonna be a storm.

32:36.748 --> 32:39.207
I don't think they were expecting
any resistance...

32:39.208 --> 32:41.752
- ...which is odd, don't you think?
- It doesn't matter.

32:41.753 --> 32:45.998
- There is a protocol we need to follow...
- Oh, fuck the protocol, Ellen!

32:47.467 --> 32:49.885
This isn't the end of it.

32:49.886 --> 32:52.471
We lost enough guys today.
I don't wanna lose more.

32:52.472 --> 32:55.974
You're a cop, right? At least you were
before you put the jacket on.

32:55.975 --> 32:58.010
What does your gut tell you?

33:08.780 --> 33:11.523
Let's see what he has to say.

33:12.075 --> 33:14.401
HALL:
You know this man?

33:15.370 --> 33:18.864
He actually just tried to kill me
to get to you.

33:19.040 --> 33:23.160
I've never seen him before,
but I know more like him will be coming.

33:23.169 --> 33:26.622
- Many more.
- Why won't you tell us your name?

33:27.382 --> 33:29.508
That is for your protection.

33:29.509 --> 33:32.135
- The less you know....
- Well...

33:32.136 --> 33:34.513
...the ink on your back's
not São Paulo Locos...

33:34.514 --> 33:38.975
...nor does it rep any of their rivals,
so you're clearly not a part of that game.

33:38.976 --> 33:41.520
My guess is you're Special Ops.

33:41.521 --> 33:44.856
You've been tortured,
from the looks of it, more than once.

33:44.857 --> 33:48.860
You could have easily escaped
our compound, but you chose not to.

33:48.861 --> 33:50.195
Why?

33:50.196 --> 33:51.780
You need our protection...

33:51.781 --> 33:54.991
...because everyone
and their mother's coming after you...

33:54.992 --> 33:57.703
...because what you know...

33:57.704 --> 33:59.705
...could cause blowback.

33:59.706 --> 34:02.124
It is far more complicated than that.

34:02.125 --> 34:03.917
Fill me in here. What am I missing?

34:03.918 --> 34:06.878
Because I believe you when you say
more like him are coming.

34:06.879 --> 34:09.130
But you're gonna have
to square-up with me...

34:09.132 --> 34:13.377
...if you want us to do more
than just turn you over.

34:15.012 --> 34:17.889
You were correct about Special Ops...

34:17.889 --> 34:20.641
...but that was only in the beginning.

34:20.643 --> 34:24.679
I quickly realized
that information was true power.

34:27.358 --> 34:31.478
- So you're a spy.
- And I have the goods on everyone.

34:32.655 --> 34:35.072
[COMPUTER WHIRRING]

34:35.074 --> 34:37.192
Hm.

34:38.870 --> 34:41.196
SIMONE:
What is it?

34:43.541 --> 34:46.241
NICHOLAS: I traced the cell phone.
LARS: Who is it?

34:46.293 --> 34:48.170
I don't have a "who"...

34:48.170 --> 34:51.665
...but I have
where the call originated from.

34:57.764 --> 35:01.550
Okay. So, what happened?
How'd you end up in our cell?

35:01.809 --> 35:03.810
I...

35:03.811 --> 35:06.480
...made a mistake in Bogotá.

35:06.481 --> 35:08.690
So why'd they capture you?
Why not kill you?

35:08.691 --> 35:10.525
To facilitate my sale.

35:10.526 --> 35:11.818
DWYER:
Bullshit.

35:11.819 --> 35:15.155
S.P.L. knows their lane. They're not
dumb enough to trade in that game.

35:15.156 --> 35:17.073
No, but others do.

35:17.074 --> 35:19.443
- Who, then?
- Unsure.

35:19.619 --> 35:21.987
But one thing I am sure of:

35:21.996 --> 35:26.283
Someone from your team is involved.

35:37.011 --> 35:39.179
LARS:
Nicholas, who are these people?

35:39.180 --> 35:42.382
Show me who we're up against.

35:42.391 --> 35:45.093
[♪♪♪]

35:59.909 --> 36:02.569
Where you going, Travis?

36:03.996 --> 36:07.115
- Commander?
- I'm moving him.

36:07.583 --> 36:09.826
Where?

36:11.796 --> 36:13.839
Not alone.
The team should be in on this.

36:13.840 --> 36:15.048
HALL:
No.

36:15.049 --> 36:17.759
- Just me.
- What, are you crazy?

36:17.760 --> 36:21.129
- That doesn't make any sense.
- Nothing about today makes sense.

36:22.682 --> 36:25.559
If I tell you where I'm going...

36:25.560 --> 36:29.596
- ...they could get it out of you.
- They wouldn't be able to.

36:31.148 --> 36:32.941
They're coming for him, Sof...

36:32.942 --> 36:35.235
...and they're not gonna stop.

36:35.236 --> 36:36.736
[♪♪♪]

36:36.737 --> 36:39.815
I won't let another person
I care about die today.

36:40.116 --> 36:43.860
If they know he's here, they could be
watching the compound, and...

36:48.416 --> 36:50.617
I'll have Elson review the area.

36:51.294 --> 36:53.579
Thanks.

36:59.969 --> 37:02.129
[KEYS JINGLING]

37:04.557 --> 37:06.099
I'm moving you.

37:06.100 --> 37:08.894
Moving me will not keep them
from coming for me.

37:08.895 --> 37:11.897
No, but it'll keep them from my team...

37:11.898 --> 37:14.016
...and that's my priority.

37:15.192 --> 37:17.311
[SIGHS]

37:21.407 --> 37:23.150
It's how it's gotta be.

37:31.584 --> 37:33.869
[♪♪♪]

37:38.215 --> 37:41.251
Yo, commander, what's going on?

37:43.763 --> 37:47.015
Hey. Just saw Hall taking Scorpion out.

37:47.016 --> 37:49.551
What do you mean, "out"?

37:50.061 --> 37:52.387
[PHONE BUZZING]

37:53.940 --> 37:55.891
It's him.

37:57.193 --> 37:58.443
Hello?

37:58.444 --> 38:02.606
MAN [IN ALTERED VOICE]: <i>Listen to me
carefully. You don't have much time.</i>

38:06.160 --> 38:07.535
How we looking?

38:07.536 --> 38:10.705
Yeah, yeah. Everything looks good.
No unusual activity.

38:10.706 --> 38:13.124
GUTIERREZ:
"Remote access error." What is that?

38:13.125 --> 38:15.085
ELSON:
That? I don't know.

38:15.086 --> 38:17.496
That has been bugging me all day.

38:17.672 --> 38:20.415
SNIPER:
<i>I'm in position.</i>

38:20.466 --> 38:22.968
Did you disable the camera
that shows our sniper?

38:22.969 --> 38:25.595
What I did was record footage
before he got there...

38:25.596 --> 38:29.057
...and just have it playing back
on a continuous loop.

38:29.058 --> 38:31.259
A simple "yes" would suffice.

38:33.020 --> 38:35.430
GUTIERREZ: Is he clear?
- Yes.

38:36.440 --> 38:38.642
Yes.

38:39.986 --> 38:43.154
- Think they're watching?
- They are definitely watching.

38:43.155 --> 38:45.448
Travis, stop!

38:45.449 --> 38:47.317
What are you doing?

38:50.871 --> 38:53.456
You said you didn't want
anyone else to die.

38:53.457 --> 38:56.368
Yeah, and that included you.

38:58.337 --> 39:01.206
I'll radio when I'm safe.

39:02.174 --> 39:04.084
Let's go.

39:05.052 --> 39:08.888
I was personally put in charge of Glen
Damone's protection. Know who that is?

39:08.889 --> 39:10.432
The mafia accountant.

39:10.433 --> 39:14.060
Trial lasted five months,
no less than 20 bounties on his head.

39:14.061 --> 39:17.597
He never got one scratch
under my watch.

39:19.066 --> 39:22.652
Wait. Wasn't he assassinated
shortly after the trial?

39:22.653 --> 39:24.696
That was on Witness Protection, not me.

39:24.697 --> 39:26.773
Watch your head.

39:27.742 --> 39:30.285
When they clear the compound,
take out the driver.

39:30.286 --> 39:33.864
- If anyone kills Scorpion, they die next.
SNIPER: <i>Roger that.</i>

39:39.378 --> 39:41.788
[♪♪♪]

39:45.384 --> 39:48.378
SNIPER: They're leaving the facility.
- Take him out.

39:53.392 --> 39:55.969
- You'd be wise to take cover.
- What?

39:56.103 --> 39:58.180
Duck!

40:09.241 --> 40:10.992
- Oh, shit.
- They're under attack.

40:10.993 --> 40:12.577
- We gotta go.
CHU: Let's move!

40:12.578 --> 40:14.120
- Where are you going?
- To help.

40:14.121 --> 40:17.461
- You're not field. Help from here.
- Find out where the backup is.

40:21.420 --> 40:23.213
WOMAN: <i>Dispatch.</i>
- This is Seattle S.W.A.T.

40:23.214 --> 40:25.882
We're under heavy attack
and need immediate assistance.

40:25.883 --> 40:27.550
<i>Roger that, Seattle S. W.A. T.</i>

40:27.551 --> 40:29.010
Hang tight.

40:29.011 --> 40:30.428
Backup's on its way.

40:30.429 --> 40:32.631
[♪♪♪]

40:45.236 --> 40:46.978
SCORPION:
Commander?

41:05.506 --> 41:08.083
MAN:
Go. Go. Go.

41:08.759 --> 41:10.877
SNIPER:
I've got the shot.

41:11.762 --> 41:13.755
[GUNSHOT]

41:14.223 --> 41:17.133
Not on my shift, motherfucker.

41:17.977 --> 41:20.679
[♪♪♪]

42:04.398 --> 42:06.024
Fuck!

42:06.025 --> 42:09.352
Do not let him get away.

42:27.922 --> 42:30.832
Commander, nice of you to join us.

42:31.550 --> 42:33.293
HALL:
Son of a bitch.

42:35.387 --> 42:37.964
Back to the compound. Move it. Now!

42:47.024 --> 42:48.975
[GUNFIRE]

42:49.735 --> 42:52.020
Holy fuck.

42:56.909 --> 42:58.451
MAN 1:
Left, left, left.

42:58.452 --> 43:01.112
- Clear.
MAN 2: Clear. Go.

43:02.456 --> 43:04.950
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

43:28.482 --> 43:30.316
MAN 3:
Get the truck out.

43:30.317 --> 43:32.277
- Everyone inside.
HOOKS: Gutierrez.

43:32.278 --> 43:34.771
- I'm on the move.
- Go, go.

43:48.419 --> 43:50.336
Dwyer, shut us down.

43:50.337 --> 43:52.505
- I'm on it.
- Shut us down now.

43:52.506 --> 43:56.126
What part of "we need him alive"
do they not understand?

44:01.640 --> 44:04.134
[KLAXON BLARING]

44:04.685 --> 44:07.554
[♪♪♪]

44:27.458 --> 44:29.083
Are those shields?

44:29.084 --> 44:31.870
Well, you have to admire their resilience.

44:33.297 --> 44:35.415
Nicholas...

44:35.507 --> 44:37.216
...can you open them?

44:37.217 --> 44:40.261
It's one thing to hack
their comms and cameras...

44:40.262 --> 44:42.513
...but shields are controlled
by the mainframe.

44:42.514 --> 44:45.016
It'd need to be taken out
before I can do anything.

44:45.017 --> 44:46.642
LARS:
Find a way past those shields.

44:46.643 --> 44:50.472
Leave the rest to me.
In the meantime, kill the power.

44:51.065 --> 44:53.516
Kill everything.

44:53.984 --> 44:58.104
Ready the next wave,
and let's see how resilient they truly are.

45:02.659 --> 45:05.028
SIMONE:
Got that?

45:10.793 --> 45:12.251
HALL:
Where's the backup, Elson?

45:12.252 --> 45:14.996
What the fuck happened?

45:18.258 --> 45:21.594
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Hold up, hold up.
What are you doing?

45:21.595 --> 45:25.932
I assure you, inspector, what's out there
is far more dangerous to you than me.

45:25.933 --> 45:28.101
They're only dangerous to us
because of you.

45:28.102 --> 45:32.055
You brought this to our door,
all of it, and I can end it right now.

45:35.943 --> 45:39.229
And you think killing me
will stop this war?

45:39.863 --> 45:42.740
Ellen, this isn't who we are.

45:42.741 --> 45:45.235
[♪♪♪]

46:09.059 --> 46:11.561
- Now what?
- What's going on, Elson?

46:11.562 --> 46:15.356
ELSON: They cut the comm and power,
and judging by the signal on my cell...

46:15.357 --> 46:18.276
- ...they're jamming the cell tower too.
- Fuck.

46:18.277 --> 46:20.903
Any satellite phones on-site?

46:20.904 --> 46:23.273
ELSON:
Yeah, none that are working.

46:24.283 --> 46:26.868
Why are cameras working
but not Internet or phones?

46:26.869 --> 46:28.661
In cases like this, you wanna see.

46:28.662 --> 46:31.038
So we put security on
the internal mainframe.

46:31.039 --> 46:33.700
And they would want to see as well.

46:33.792 --> 46:35.543
They hacked the security cameras.

46:35.544 --> 46:37.879
- They can do that?
- It's not that hard.

46:37.880 --> 46:40.540
For somebody who's good enough,
it's not.

46:41.425 --> 46:43.259
HALL:
Cut the interior security cameras.

46:43.260 --> 46:46.713
- Don't let them see what we're doing.
ELSON: Copy that.

46:54.104 --> 46:55.855
SCORPION:
Get this through your skulls.

46:55.856 --> 46:59.442
These are professional soldiers.
They will isolate you, intimidate you...

46:59.443 --> 47:02.854
...until they find your weakest link
and then exploit it.

47:02.988 --> 47:05.565
[PHONE RINGING]

47:07.117 --> 47:10.945
- I thought you said the phones were out.
- They are.

47:17.127 --> 47:18.336
HALL:
<i>Hello?</i>

47:18.337 --> 47:19.545
LARS:
Commander Hall?

47:19.546 --> 47:21.297
<i>Yeah.</i>

47:21.298 --> 47:25.676
I'm the man in control of the small army
sitting on your doorstep.

47:25.677 --> 47:28.095
<i>Do you have a moment to chat?</i>

47:28.096 --> 47:30.890
<i>If you want to put me on speaker,
go ahead. I understand.</i>

47:30.891 --> 47:33.676
<i>Everyone should hear.</i>

47:36.647 --> 47:38.356
[OVER SPEAKERPHONE]
<i>I should've done this earlier.</i>

47:38.357 --> 47:41.776
<i>It would've saved us all
a lot of time, sweat...</i>

47:41.777 --> 47:43.945
<i>...and blood.</i>

47:43.946 --> 47:45.613
I have your compound surrounded.

47:45.614 --> 47:47.156
Your power, your network...

47:47.157 --> 47:49.859
<i>...all of your communications are down.</i>

47:49.993 --> 47:53.371
<i>No one knows that you're in trouble,
and no one's coming to help.</i>

47:53.372 --> 47:56.541
<i>Your officer spoke
to my associate, Simone...</i>

47:56.542 --> 47:59.252
...not the dispatch operator.

47:59.253 --> 48:01.579
Hello.

48:02.089 --> 48:05.458
The man you pulled
out of a box belongs to me.

48:05.759 --> 48:07.969
<i>Hand him over...</i>

48:07.970 --> 48:09.428
<i>...and I'll go away.</i>

48:09.429 --> 48:10.888
Just like that?

48:10.889 --> 48:14.717
<i>Just like that.</i>

48:16.436 --> 48:18.805
Can't do it.

48:20.983 --> 48:23.476
Scorpion...

48:23.569 --> 48:25.319
<i>...I know you're listening.</i>

48:25.320 --> 48:28.815
<i>Tell these people who I am.</i>

48:28.949 --> 48:31.367
His name is Lars Cohagen.

48:31.368 --> 48:33.703
He runs a private military corporation...

48:33.704 --> 48:38.324
- ...that specializes in dark ops.
- The kind that overthrow small countries?

48:38.750 --> 48:41.794
- Some not so small.
- Hm.

48:41.795 --> 48:43.421
LARS:
<i>Now that we're all in the know...</i>

48:43.422 --> 48:47.216
<i>...why don't you come on out and
spare the lives of these nice people?</i>

48:47.217 --> 48:50.586
Let them return home
and enjoy what's left of the holiday.

48:51.805 --> 48:54.215
They could still catch the fireworks.

48:55.350 --> 48:57.435
How many times
are we going to do this?

48:57.436 --> 48:59.929
This is it.

49:00.147 --> 49:02.473
This is our last dance.

49:02.649 --> 49:04.851
I've heard this before.

49:04.943 --> 49:08.904
<i>Commander Hall, the man
you're protecting is a consummate liar.</i>

49:08.905 --> 49:11.157
His skills of deception
supersede even mine.

49:11.158 --> 49:16.362
In fact, I will guarantee
that he's lying to you right now.

49:16.747 --> 49:20.742
<i>Has he told you there's one
in your organization that's against you?</i>

49:20.917 --> 49:24.829
<i>Or that he has information
that could set the world ablaze?</i>

49:25.297 --> 49:27.006
<i>He's a liar...</i>

49:27.007 --> 49:29.592
...and a killer and nothing more.

49:29.593 --> 49:32.970
All your problems go away if you just...

49:32.971 --> 49:34.756
...turn him over.

49:37.184 --> 49:39.560
And I already told you...

49:39.561 --> 49:41.471
...I'm not doing that.

49:42.814 --> 49:44.023
SIMONE:
Commander...

49:44.024 --> 49:48.728
...so this stranger's life is more
important to you than your team's?

49:48.737 --> 49:51.773
What about Daniel Chu?

49:51.782 --> 49:53.532
<i>David Jefferson?</i>

49:53.533 --> 49:56.952
<i>Luis and Maria Gutierrez?</i>

49:56.953 --> 49:59.405
Carley and Rebecca?

50:00.832 --> 50:04.327
Is Scorpion's life worth more to you
than their lives?

50:05.462 --> 50:10.041
Are all their lives
worth Scorpion's to you?

50:10.175 --> 50:12.960
[♪♪♪]

50:14.680 --> 50:17.682
Enough. I'm coming out.

50:17.683 --> 50:19.558
<i>But before I do...</i>

50:19.559 --> 50:21.060
...I want your guarantee.

50:21.061 --> 50:24.972
No harm comes to anyone here,
nor their families.

50:25.857 --> 50:27.725
You have my word.

50:28.026 --> 50:30.319
I will be out in 10 minutes.

50:30.320 --> 50:32.146
<i>You'd better be.</i>

50:36.368 --> 50:40.780
ELSON: Commander, try the phone
again. Maybe we have a live line out.

50:42.791 --> 50:44.709
HALL:
No.

50:44.710 --> 50:47.036
Shit.

50:52.426 --> 50:55.177
HALL: You're not giving yourself up.
SCORPION: I never said I was.

50:55.178 --> 50:56.762
I only said I was coming out.

50:56.763 --> 50:59.640
- You think you can take his army alone?
- I work best alone.

50:59.641 --> 51:02.435
With the shields down,
this place can withstand a riot.

51:02.436 --> 51:03.644
You don't have to go.

51:03.645 --> 51:06.230
WARD:
Well, hold on a second. I'm confused.

51:06.231 --> 51:08.315
- You giving yourself up or not?
- He's not.

51:08.316 --> 51:10.109
- We can't let him.
HOOKS: Yes, we can.

51:10.110 --> 51:12.478
Did you not see that army out there?

51:12.988 --> 51:15.781
We just lost Phil and Benson.

51:15.782 --> 51:18.576
I don't plan to join them
because of this son of a bitch.

51:18.577 --> 51:19.994
You heard him, commander.

51:19.995 --> 51:22.705
He's threatening our families,
and there's no backup.

51:22.706 --> 51:25.833
This guy's a fucking liar.
He could be playing us. Let him go.

51:25.834 --> 51:28.794
No. We're not giving in
to this Lars asshole.

51:28.795 --> 51:30.713
Not after all that's happened.

51:30.714 --> 51:33.299
It ain't his fault
a lunatic's shooting the building.

51:33.300 --> 51:34.592
Maybe it is. We don't know.

51:34.593 --> 51:37.261
Scorpion could've escaped
or killed us several times.

51:37.262 --> 51:38.596
He didn't. I believe him.

51:38.597 --> 51:41.474
That just might mean
that he needed our help to survive.

51:41.475 --> 51:43.392
That doesn't disprove what Lars said.

51:43.393 --> 51:46.061
Believe Lars when he says
he will stop at nothing...

51:46.062 --> 51:48.105
...to find a way inside to get me.

51:48.106 --> 51:50.858
If I do not come out now,
that army outside...

51:50.859 --> 51:53.068
...those phony agents...

51:53.069 --> 51:55.605
...they are just the tip of the iceberg.

52:01.453 --> 52:03.696
You're right.

52:04.456 --> 52:06.741
We'll put you by the back door.

52:07.459 --> 52:10.161
Only it won't be you.

52:17.761 --> 52:21.180
In theory, it should work. I loaded
everything you need on the laptop.

52:21.181 --> 52:23.557
You should be good to go.

52:23.558 --> 52:26.352
I wanna thank you
for your assistance today, Nicholas.

52:26.353 --> 52:29.013
Oh, my pleasure, sir.

52:29.356 --> 52:32.767
Did you know that Scorpion and I
used to be partners?

52:32.901 --> 52:34.276
Right. You were saying.

52:34.277 --> 52:36.195
It was great for a while...

52:36.196 --> 52:39.198
...and then five years ago in Berlin,
he betrayed me.

52:39.199 --> 52:41.275
After all we'd been through.

52:41.493 --> 52:43.536
You know, and I knew it.

52:43.537 --> 52:46.539
I knew something was wrong,
but I didn't react in time.

52:46.540 --> 52:51.752
Since then, I've taken greater precaution
in my business dealings because...

52:51.753 --> 52:56.541
...no matter how much you think
you know someone...

52:57.133 --> 53:00.086
...they could stab you in the back.

53:00.637 --> 53:03.714
Do you understand what I'm saying?

53:03.723 --> 53:05.975
Um....

53:05.976 --> 53:08.636
Yeah, I think so.

53:11.147 --> 53:12.932
Good.

53:17.320 --> 53:19.572
WARD:
All right, let me get this straight.

53:19.573 --> 53:22.283
You wanna raise the door shields
and let the army in?

53:22.284 --> 53:25.452
Not let them in.
Lure them close, then ambush them.

53:25.453 --> 53:26.704
Why won't that work?

53:26.705 --> 53:28.664
Because it's batshit crazy.

53:28.665 --> 53:31.917
HALL: Well, there's no way we're turning
this man over to mercenaries.

53:31.918 --> 53:34.253
Once they're in the courtyard,
they're trapped.

53:34.254 --> 53:36.213
How do you figure that?

53:36.214 --> 53:40.926
The back door is located
in the deepest part of the courtyard.

53:40.927 --> 53:42.136
Here.

53:42.137 --> 53:45.931
Now, about three dozen
office windows look down onto it.

53:45.932 --> 53:47.641
That's where we'll be.

53:47.642 --> 53:50.761
We'll make them think
we're handing you over.

53:50.896 --> 53:55.190
To sell it, Elson will find a way
to open the rear entrance shield.

53:55.191 --> 53:56.984
Once they get eyes on the bait...

53:56.985 --> 54:01.322
...they're gonna move in
underneath our hidden positions...

54:01.323 --> 54:03.532
...and that's when we hit them.

54:03.533 --> 54:04.950
They'll be sitting ducks.

54:04.951 --> 54:08.078
It's the first time
the shields have ever been activated.

54:08.079 --> 54:09.288
I've never done...

54:09.289 --> 54:12.541
...nor am I sure isolated openings
will work as you describe them.

54:12.542 --> 54:15.411
Yeah. Well, you'll figure it out.

54:16.630 --> 54:18.047
They'll be expecting that.

54:18.048 --> 54:20.758
HALL:
Yeah. Well, this is our only option.

54:20.759 --> 54:22.092
They got us boxed in.

54:22.093 --> 54:25.638
We can't call out,
and you said it yourself.

54:25.639 --> 54:28.223
It's only a matter of time
till he finds his way in.

54:28.224 --> 54:31.344
At least this way, it's on our own terms.

54:32.270 --> 54:35.230
Look, guys, this isn't an order.

54:35.231 --> 54:37.066
I'm not forcing you into this.

54:37.067 --> 54:42.488
But I, for one, don't wanna sit around
and let someone else determine my fate.

54:42.489 --> 54:44.490
If I'm going out...

54:44.491 --> 54:48.577
...it's gonna be on my terms, not theirs.

54:48.578 --> 54:51.280
[♪♪♪]

54:57.671 --> 55:02.249
If this is what you want,
I will need firepower.

55:04.636 --> 55:06.679
HALL:
We have every weapon known to man.

55:06.680 --> 55:08.389
What exactly are you looking for?

55:08.390 --> 55:11.717
SCORPION: I will know it when I see it.
- We aim to please.

55:12.394 --> 55:15.012
In the meantime,
spread out and load up.

55:18.066 --> 55:21.435
Just because I'm browsing
don't mean I'm giving up on you.

55:28.660 --> 55:30.945
What the fuck do you do with that?

55:31.663 --> 55:33.872
You don't want anything
to do with that.

55:33.873 --> 55:36.492
That's when you got nothing to live for.

55:37.502 --> 55:39.245
Huh.

55:43.133 --> 55:44.466
YORK:
Hey.

55:44.467 --> 55:47.628
Oh. Never mind.

55:48.638 --> 55:51.215
SCORPION:
What did you find?

55:52.350 --> 55:54.601
- Excellent.
WARD: Why?

55:54.602 --> 55:56.562
Regular radios still work.

55:56.563 --> 55:58.647
He may have tapped
into those frequencies.

55:58.648 --> 56:00.858
He will not be able to do so
with this model.

56:00.859 --> 56:04.311
Okay. Everyone grab one.

56:04.821 --> 56:06.939
You gotta change.

56:12.370 --> 56:14.913
HALL: How'd you get the name Scorpion,
anyway?

56:14.914 --> 56:18.909
I assume that's not
on your birth certificate.

56:18.918 --> 56:22.913
You are assuming
I have a birth certificate.

56:23.006 --> 56:25.257
All right, you're not gonna
tell me your name.

56:25.258 --> 56:29.462
At least you can tell me
how you know Lars Cohagen.

56:29.554 --> 56:32.298
We were once partners.

56:32.474 --> 56:35.176
[♪♪♪]

56:35.393 --> 56:39.346
I never said I was a good man,
commander, just good at what I do.

56:44.861 --> 56:47.029
You do not know me, commander.

56:47.030 --> 56:49.106
You should not take this risk.

56:49.616 --> 56:51.525
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

56:56.164 --> 57:00.534
Even holiday double-time ain't enough
to deal with this shit today.

57:01.503 --> 57:05.631
You know, the job is risk.

57:05.632 --> 57:08.175
It's not about or for you.

57:08.176 --> 57:10.878
Not any longer.

57:10.887 --> 57:14.381
Our guys' blood's been spilled today.

57:14.390 --> 57:16.425
Someone's gonna pay for that.

57:19.229 --> 57:21.138
[♪♪♪]

57:34.244 --> 57:37.363
SCORPION: <i>There is one thing
you have not addressed.</i>

57:39.499 --> 57:42.876
The person on the inside
who is working against us.

57:42.877 --> 57:45.879
When they attacked the van,
they were waiting for us.

57:45.880 --> 57:49.166
Someone told Lars
you were taking me from the compound.

57:51.845 --> 57:53.554
GUTIERREZ [OVER RADIO]:
<i>Two-minute warning.</i>

57:53.555 --> 57:55.597
Copy that. Everyone get in position.

57:55.598 --> 57:59.017
- We go on my call.
- Copy that.

57:59.018 --> 58:00.227
Good luck.

58:00.228 --> 58:03.480
Never really believed in luck.

58:03.481 --> 58:05.774
Well, good luck anyway.

58:05.775 --> 58:08.477
[♪♪♪]

58:21.416 --> 58:23.375
Everyone set?
Know what they're doing?

58:23.376 --> 58:24.793
ALL:
Yes, sir.

58:24.794 --> 58:26.871
Yes, sir.

58:28.047 --> 58:30.632
Sof, you remember Suffolk,
a few years back?

58:30.633 --> 58:32.376
Yeah.

58:32.468 --> 58:35.679
That was another
supposedly cakewalk mission...

58:35.680 --> 58:38.348
...that turned into a shitshow.

58:38.349 --> 58:42.144
What was it, 40 gangbangers
against eight S.W.A.T.?

58:42.145 --> 58:45.681
I tell people I never know
how we survived that night.

58:47.150 --> 58:49.393
But I do know.

58:50.570 --> 58:52.897
We're S.W.A.T.

58:53.781 --> 58:56.400
We're the baddest motherfuckers
on Earth.

58:58.578 --> 59:01.196
Let's get in position.

59:02.207 --> 59:04.491
Take care of each other.

59:07.670 --> 59:11.965
The least he could do is give us
the microchip to barter for our lives.

59:11.966 --> 59:15.127
There's no microchip. It's in his head.

59:16.804 --> 59:20.257
- Hey, make sure we're in position
before... DWYER: Hey.

59:20.308 --> 59:22.134
It's not my first rodeo.

59:22.185 --> 59:24.678
Don't fuck up.

59:28.775 --> 59:29.983
How we looking?

59:29.984 --> 59:33.737
When we get the go, I hit enter,
and it'll raise the rear-entrance shield.

59:33.738 --> 59:37.366
- But not the rest of the building?
- Right. Just the rear entrance.

59:37.367 --> 59:39.201
In theory.

59:39.202 --> 59:41.536
In theory?

59:41.537 --> 59:43.781
In theory.

59:44.040 --> 59:46.742
[♪♪♪]

59:52.090 --> 59:53.632
MAN 1:
Position. Hold that position.

59:53.633 --> 59:54.925
MAN 2:
All right, let's go.

59:54.926 --> 59:56.752
MAN 1:
Left, left, left.

01:00:02.934 --> 01:00:05.594
SIMONE:
No sign of Scorpion.

01:00:07.105 --> 01:00:09.064
Commander, is your team ready?

01:00:09.065 --> 01:00:10.941
Let's go around the horn.

01:00:10.942 --> 01:00:12.818
Hooks, set.

01:00:12.819 --> 01:00:15.737
- Jefferson, set.
- York, set.

01:00:15.738 --> 01:00:18.399
- Gutierrez, set.
CHU: <i>Chu, set.</i>

01:00:21.286 --> 01:00:24.071
Ward, are you in position?

01:00:25.540 --> 01:00:27.666
Ward?

01:00:27.667 --> 01:00:29.910
Sorry, I was using the wrong mic.

01:00:30.420 --> 01:00:32.371
We're all set.

01:00:33.089 --> 01:00:36.583
- Raise the shield.
- Copy.

01:00:41.431 --> 01:00:44.675
[KLAXON BLARING]

01:00:50.857 --> 01:00:53.267
It worked.

01:00:54.944 --> 01:00:57.279
SIMONE:
Right on time.

01:00:57.280 --> 01:01:01.191
They're opening the shields
by the rear entrance. Move in.

01:01:24.515 --> 01:01:27.217
HALL:
<i>Here they come. Get ready.</i>

01:01:33.941 --> 01:01:36.351
SIMONE:
Third-floor window.

01:01:36.527 --> 01:01:38.437
What is that?

01:01:41.240 --> 01:01:43.734
Morse code.

01:01:46.412 --> 01:01:48.747
- Pull everyone back.
- It's a trap.

01:01:48.748 --> 01:01:50.957
<i>Everyone move back. Now.</i>

01:01:50.958 --> 01:01:54.453
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
He's stopping. Why is he stopping?

01:01:55.588 --> 01:01:57.414
Hey.

01:01:57.507 --> 01:01:59.917
HALL:
What the fuck just happened?

01:02:00.593 --> 01:02:02.677
Fall back to the command center.

01:02:02.678 --> 01:02:05.089
GUTIERREZ:
<i>Copy. Everyone fall back.</i>

01:02:11.521 --> 01:02:13.680
Fuck.

01:02:14.899 --> 01:02:18.560
- Elson, shut down the rear shields.
- I'm on it.

01:02:19.862 --> 01:02:21.988
- Where's everybody?
- Ward, I don't know.

01:02:21.989 --> 01:02:23.198
Scorpion's M.I.A.

01:02:23.199 --> 01:02:25.784
- Dwyer left a few minutes ago.
- Where?

01:02:25.785 --> 01:02:27.911
We saw a light
at the third-floor window...

01:02:27.912 --> 01:02:30.288
- ...and she bolted.
- A light? Which window?

01:02:30.289 --> 01:02:32.699
Right there.

01:02:34.377 --> 01:02:36.670
Stay here.
Keep an eye on everything outside.

01:02:36.671 --> 01:02:40.082
- Where are you going?
- Find the big guy.

01:02:40.258 --> 01:02:42.835
Scorpion, come in.

01:02:43.928 --> 01:02:46.713
Scorpion, do you copy?

01:02:46.848 --> 01:02:49.383
[WHISTLING]

01:02:50.393 --> 01:02:52.594
Get up.

01:02:59.694 --> 01:03:02.354
I'm gonna let you out of here.

01:03:02.613 --> 01:03:07.109
You're gonna tell Lars I'm gonna find
another way to give him Scorpion.

01:03:08.035 --> 01:03:09.578
No one else needs to die.

01:03:09.579 --> 01:03:12.281
Shit, it was you.

01:03:12.582 --> 01:03:15.208
Yeah, I'll tell him. Lead the way.

01:03:15.209 --> 01:03:18.962
WARD: The amount is the same upon delivery.
Fifty million. That hasn't changed.

01:03:18.963 --> 01:03:21.882
Fifty million's
a sweet fucking payday for a cop.

01:03:21.883 --> 01:03:24.384
Those DEA assholes
are always skimming off the top.

01:03:24.385 --> 01:03:26.887
- About time I got some. Hey.
- Of course it is.

01:03:26.888 --> 01:03:29.764
This mess is Hall's fault.
If he had handed over Scorpion...

01:03:29.765 --> 01:03:32.434
What the hell's the plan
on getting me out of here?

01:03:32.435 --> 01:03:34.644
We're gonna cut the power
to the mainframe.

01:03:34.645 --> 01:03:37.022
With shields up,
Lars can take care of the rest.

01:03:37.023 --> 01:03:39.191
- Where are the controls?
- Engineering room.

01:03:39.192 --> 01:03:41.026
Thanks.

01:03:41.027 --> 01:03:42.444
DWYER:
Ward?

01:03:42.445 --> 01:03:43.653
[NECK SNAPS]

01:03:43.654 --> 01:03:45.906
[GROANING]

01:03:45.907 --> 01:03:48.483
[♪♪♪]

01:03:50.703 --> 01:03:52.821
Fuck.

01:04:16.437 --> 01:04:18.271
HALL:
Ellen.

01:04:18.272 --> 01:04:20.432
Oh....

01:04:20.483 --> 01:04:23.143
- You all right?
- Yeah.

01:04:25.947 --> 01:04:27.280
It was Ward.

01:04:27.281 --> 01:04:30.609
I saw him talking to Franklin
before Franklin killed him.

01:04:31.702 --> 01:04:34.363
- Where'd he go?
- In there.

01:04:37.625 --> 01:04:40.118
- Yeah.
- Ready?

01:05:09.407 --> 01:05:11.692
What's that?

01:05:19.709 --> 01:05:22.168
CHU: What just happened?
- Security feed's been cut.

01:05:22.169 --> 01:05:24.796
- We're blind outside now too.
- You said the feed was internal.

01:05:24.797 --> 01:05:26.923
It is.

01:05:26.924 --> 01:05:30.010
- I've lost control of our security system.
- What's that mean?

01:05:30.011 --> 01:05:34.556
What I mean is the same crazy fuck that's
been attacking us can open our shields...

01:05:34.557 --> 01:05:37.884
...and there is nothing
that we can do about it.

01:05:45.526 --> 01:05:48.478
[CLATTERING]

01:05:49.989 --> 01:05:52.115
Closer.

01:05:52.116 --> 01:05:54.151
Clear.

01:05:56.621 --> 01:05:58.905
[KLAXON BLARING]

01:06:01.876 --> 01:06:04.127
- What the fuck is happening?
- The shields are raising.

01:06:04.128 --> 01:06:06.997
YORK: Can you stop it?
ELSON: No.

01:06:17.475 --> 01:06:19.885
[♪♪♪]

01:06:22.438 --> 01:06:25.349
FRANKLIN:
What are you gonna fucking do, huh?

01:06:28.861 --> 01:06:30.854
Oh, yeah.

01:06:48.339 --> 01:06:50.290
DWYER:
Travis.

01:06:56.138 --> 01:06:59.508
[GUNSHOTS]

01:07:10.903 --> 01:07:13.939
SIMONE:
Intel from Berlin.

01:07:19.078 --> 01:07:21.579
Dead or alive no longer matters.

01:07:21.580 --> 01:07:26.584
I will go in there
and fucking kill him myself if I have to.

01:07:26.585 --> 01:07:28.870
Go!

01:07:29.755 --> 01:07:31.089
Everyone, move in.

01:07:31.090 --> 01:07:33.717
<i>Shoot to kill Scorpion on sight.</i>

01:07:33.718 --> 01:07:34.968
MAN:
Let's go.

01:07:34.969 --> 01:07:36.962
[♪♪♪]

01:07:37.346 --> 01:07:39.923
Oh, shit.

01:07:44.061 --> 01:07:46.596
- Everyone fall back. Let's go.
- Come on.

01:07:46.814 --> 01:07:49.224
HALL:
Go, go, go.

01:08:07.501 --> 01:08:09.828
Elson, come on.

01:08:13.382 --> 01:08:14.716
MAN:
After those guys.

01:08:14.717 --> 01:08:16.835
Let's go.

01:08:17.678 --> 01:08:19.679
Clear.

01:08:19.680 --> 01:08:21.680
Move, move, move.

01:08:21.682 --> 01:08:23.508
Let's go. Let's go.

01:08:32.067 --> 01:08:33.852
Man down!

01:08:34.904 --> 01:08:37.354
[♪♪♪]

01:08:46.415 --> 01:08:48.158
HOOKS:
Jefferson, come on.

01:08:52.296 --> 01:08:54.456
Jefferson.

01:09:07.228 --> 01:09:09.595
Go.

01:09:17.904 --> 01:09:20.607
[JEFFERSON GROANING]

01:09:22.033 --> 01:09:24.027
Later, bitches.

01:09:24.118 --> 01:09:26.821
[EXPLOSION]

01:09:33.504 --> 01:09:35.622
[♪♪♪]

01:10:23.387 --> 01:10:26.423
Get over yourself.

01:10:30.352 --> 01:10:33.054
[♪♪♪]

01:10:35.441 --> 01:10:37.726
Let's go. Go.

01:10:49.163 --> 01:10:50.989
Duck.

01:11:07.723 --> 01:11:09.766
HALL:
Oh.

01:11:09.767 --> 01:11:12.226
You meant that kind of firepower.

01:11:12.227 --> 01:11:14.354
SCORPION:
I have something to show you.

01:11:14.355 --> 01:11:15.730
The way out.

01:11:15.731 --> 01:11:17.899
I found a maintenance tunnel.

01:11:17.900 --> 01:11:20.026
HALL:
Yeah, it's been sealed.

01:11:20.027 --> 01:11:21.853
SCORPION:
Not anymore.

01:11:24.281 --> 01:11:27.283
- Nope. Fuck that.
- Hey, it's either that...

01:11:27.284 --> 01:11:31.655
...or you go back out there to face a bunch
of badass dudes shooting at you.

01:11:31.956 --> 01:11:35.617
- All right, give me a boost.
- Okay.

01:11:36.502 --> 01:11:38.127
Fuck.

01:11:38.128 --> 01:11:40.622
CHU: Right behind you, Elson.
- Okay.

01:11:42.257 --> 01:11:45.760
- Travis.
- I'm going after Dwyer.

01:11:45.761 --> 01:11:48.304
No way I'm leaving
one of our own behind.

01:11:48.305 --> 01:11:50.014
Get them to safety, okay?

01:11:50.015 --> 01:11:52.809
You don't know how many
of them are still up there.

01:11:52.810 --> 01:11:55.561
- Or if she's even alive.
- I'm gonna be fine.

01:11:55.562 --> 01:11:58.098
- Go on.
- I'm not letting you go alone.

01:11:58.440 --> 01:12:00.892
He won't be.

01:12:02.569 --> 01:12:05.730
I'll call for backup as soon as I can.

01:12:08.367 --> 01:12:10.743
- You don't have to do this.
- I know.

01:12:10.744 --> 01:12:14.280
You didn't have to come back just for us.

01:12:14.665 --> 01:12:16.866
I didn't.

01:12:23.048 --> 01:12:25.341
HALL:
Looks like everybody cleared out.

01:12:25.342 --> 01:12:27.093
[♪♪♪]

01:12:27.094 --> 01:12:28.720
SCORPION:
Unlikely.

01:12:28.721 --> 01:12:31.589
Lars would never give up.

01:12:54.788 --> 01:12:57.615
[GUNSHOTS]

01:12:58.792 --> 01:13:01.494
[♪♪♪]

01:13:16.810 --> 01:13:18.511
[GRUNTS]

01:13:57.726 --> 01:13:59.469
[GUN CLICKS]

01:14:15.244 --> 01:14:17.153
At least I got you.

01:14:21.667 --> 01:14:24.577
Now let us see if you can finish the job.

01:14:26.880 --> 01:14:29.582
[♪♪♪]

01:15:13.760 --> 01:15:15.503
[SCORPION YELLING]

01:15:27.065 --> 01:15:29.392
[BODY THUDS]

01:15:55.344 --> 01:15:58.046
[♪♪♪]

01:16:11.151 --> 01:16:14.395
[♪♪♪]

01:16:22.204 --> 01:16:24.489
Hey.

01:16:24.873 --> 01:16:26.582
Hey.

01:16:26.583 --> 01:16:29.702
- What happened?
- It's over.

01:16:29.962 --> 01:16:32.789
Good guys won. Come on.

01:16:36.176 --> 01:16:38.052
HALL:
We lost York and Jefferson.

01:16:38.053 --> 01:16:39.845
DWYER: Oh, God, no.
- Yeah.

01:16:39.846 --> 01:16:43.224
DWYER: What about Scorpion?
- Yeah, he's still alive...

01:16:43.225 --> 01:16:45.426
...somehow.

01:17:00.951 --> 01:17:03.286
- Still no signal?
HALL: Mm.

01:17:03.287 --> 01:17:06.656
Gutierrez said she'd call it in
when they got out.

01:17:06.790 --> 01:17:10.118
Cell towers must still be jammed...

01:17:10.460 --> 01:17:13.254
...but it shouldn't be too long now...

01:17:13.255 --> 01:17:15.923
...which means you need to disappear.

01:17:15.924 --> 01:17:18.551
I don't know if I have it in me
to run anymore.

01:17:18.552 --> 01:17:20.845
I am constantly running.

01:17:20.846 --> 01:17:23.673
That and all the people
trying to kill me...

01:17:24.808 --> 01:17:27.184
...it's exhausting.

01:17:27.185 --> 01:17:30.646
You got all that money in your head.
Why not just retire?

01:17:30.647 --> 01:17:32.682
That is blood money.

01:17:33.692 --> 01:17:34.900
[♪♪♪]

01:17:34.901 --> 01:17:37.812
As a matter of fact....

01:17:40.365 --> 01:17:42.275
Dude, what the fuck?

01:17:46.663 --> 01:17:48.247
SCORPION:
Take it.

01:17:48.248 --> 01:17:50.249
What the hell is it?

01:17:50.250 --> 01:17:53.161
SCORPION:
It's what all the fuss is about.

01:17:53.754 --> 01:17:55.621
A microchip.

01:17:56.590 --> 01:17:59.967
What's in your head. That's clever.

01:17:59.968 --> 01:18:03.880
And now it's better in your hands.

01:18:08.894 --> 01:18:12.480
DWYER: <i>Late last night, a shipping
container arrived at Monfell from Bogotá.</i>

01:18:12.481 --> 01:18:16.434
Yeah, what'd he turn out to be?
A guy in a box.

01:18:16.485 --> 01:18:20.696
<i>The least he could do is give us
the microchip to barter for our lives.</i>

01:18:20.697 --> 01:18:23.107
HALL:
<i>There's no microchip.</i>

01:18:25.077 --> 01:18:27.779
[♪♪♪]

01:18:37.381 --> 01:18:40.958
- Ellen, what are you doing?
- It's nothing personal, Travis.

01:18:46.515 --> 01:18:50.101
You should have just handed
Scorpion over, Travis.

01:18:50.102 --> 01:18:53.679
No one was supposed to get hurt.
You should've just let it go.

01:20:42.964 --> 01:20:45.041
Don't.

01:20:49.137 --> 01:20:51.047
Don't.

01:20:51.640 --> 01:20:54.008
It's over.

01:21:05.237 --> 01:21:07.939
[♪♪♪]

01:21:19.167 --> 01:21:21.869
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

01:21:35.225 --> 01:21:37.551
MAN:
What did I say?

01:21:43.650 --> 01:21:46.102
- Good?
- Yeah.

01:21:52.117 --> 01:21:53.909
GUTIERREZ:
FBI was onto her.

01:21:53.910 --> 01:21:56.195
And she knew.

01:22:02.460 --> 01:22:04.954
I never liked her.

01:22:10.510 --> 01:22:12.878
What is that?

01:22:14.764 --> 01:22:17.174
A souvenir.

01:22:23.773 --> 01:22:25.941
AGENT:
Excuse me, commander.

01:22:25.942 --> 01:22:29.061
Can I ask you to come
and identify the body?

01:22:46.713 --> 01:22:49.173
Is this the man known as Scorpion?

01:22:49.174 --> 01:22:51.500
[♪♪♪]

01:22:52.927 --> 01:22:54.219
- That's...
- That's him.

01:22:54.220 --> 01:22:57.048
AGENT:
Okay. Take him away, guys.

01:23:08.109 --> 01:23:10.444
GUTIERREZ:
Is there something you wanna tell me?

01:23:10.445 --> 01:23:14.156
HALL: Yeah, but for your protection,
I'd better not.

01:23:14.157 --> 01:23:16.901
The less you know....

01:23:17.077 --> 01:23:18.285
[♪♪♪]

01:23:18.286 --> 01:23:19.536
HALL:
<i>Hey, hon.</i>

01:23:19.537 --> 01:23:21.997
<i>- How's the party going?</i>
CARLEY: <i>Travis, oh, my God.</i>

01:23:21.998 --> 01:23:26.001
<i>- I've been worried sick. Are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm... I'm fine. I'm on my way.</i>

01:23:26.002 --> 01:23:30.247
<i>I'll tell you about it
when I get up there, okay? I love you.</i>

01:23:42.352 --> 01:23:46.063
CARLEY: Purple.
BECKY: P-U-R-P-L-E.

01:23:46.064 --> 01:23:49.066
- Three.
- One, two, three.

01:23:49.067 --> 01:23:51.110
- Four.
- Four.

01:23:51.111 --> 01:23:53.396
[CARLEY LAUGHING]

01:23:53.697 --> 01:23:55.439
HALL:
Wow.

01:23:55.824 --> 01:23:57.574
Hi, Daddy.

01:23:57.575 --> 01:24:01.278
- Hi, sweetheart.
- You look like you could use a beer.

01:24:01.746 --> 01:24:04.448
Or 20.

01:24:06.000 --> 01:24:08.252
- Hey.
- Hey, what's this?

01:24:08.253 --> 01:24:10.454
Yeah.

01:24:13.967 --> 01:24:16.210
This is enough.

01:24:17.220 --> 01:24:18.929
For me.

01:24:18.930 --> 01:24:20.806
Just you...

01:24:20.807 --> 01:24:22.891
...and her.

01:24:22.892 --> 01:24:25.845
I don't need anything more.

01:24:27.272 --> 01:24:29.390
But I'm pregnant.

01:24:30.191 --> 01:24:32.359
[LAUGHS]

01:24:32.360 --> 01:24:35.070
- Are you kidding me?
- Surprise.

01:24:35.071 --> 01:24:37.148
[BOTH LAUGHING]

01:24:40.118 --> 01:24:43.320
- Is that what you were trying to tell me?
- Yeah.

01:24:43.413 --> 01:24:45.164
Did you know about this?

01:24:45.165 --> 01:24:46.623
Yeah, I could tell.

01:24:46.624 --> 01:24:49.285
The two of you....

01:24:50.336 --> 01:24:52.913
[FIREWORKS POPPING]

01:24:57.302 --> 01:24:59.462
[♪♪♪]

01:25:43.139 --> 01:25:45.508
[PHONE RINGING]

01:25:46.476 --> 01:25:47.893
HALL:
<i>Hall here.</i>

01:25:47.894 --> 01:25:51.855
DISPATCHER: <i>We got a shitshow
brewing at the capitol building in Olympia.</i>

01:25:51.856 --> 01:25:56.227
<i>We need you
and your team on-scene ASAP.</i>

01:25:58.154 --> 01:26:00.439
[♪♪♪]

